I think it's a bunch of papercuts adding up. The mana rock is an automatic staple, which doesn't feel super fun. It's limited availability, also not great. There's a new bant commander who's bonkers stupid. These are coming out as a product for a format we don't support, so these cards feel like they're for us, but not for us. And WotC will see the high demand on these products, when we're buying them for a 2-mana artifact, and say that people must really like Brawl, and then make more decks like this with more cards like this

It's there, you don't have to play it, similarly to Grim Monolith or Mana Vault. THe cards to boost your decks are there if you want to spend the money on it. The rock is similar.
The commander on the other hand; Yeah, nah, snoozefest. It's another Meren.
Or Tatyova
or Yarok

There's a significant difference between the 'optimization' of a Mana Vault and the optimization of a Signet

Only if you think of it that way though. The only difference is what they are called. They both help your deck become more efficient. One we are used to being easily accessable and available, and the other is a higher end card. You don't have to run either, but they are both options.
The option for the rock should be there, just like the option for Command Tower should be there imo
